value.title: Rep. Elissa Slotkin of Michigan reportedly eyed as Biden's CIA director
value.excerpt: U.S. Rep. Elissa Slotkin of Michigan is reportedly among those under consideration to head the CIA in President-elect Joe Biden's administration.

value.title: Trump to give first post-2020 election interview to Fox’s Maria Bartiromo Sunday
value.excerpt: Maria Bartiromo will interview President Trump on Fox Business on Sunday morning — his first since the election.

value.title: Trump continues fight in Wis., Pa.: ‘We have found many illegal votes’
value.excerpt: President Trump promised to bring a case disputing the Wisconsin vote count after the recount was completed there, and said his campaign was disputing a number of votes far bigger than the margin President-elect Joe Biden won.

value.title: Kamala Harris scoops up gifts, promotes small businesses at holiday market
value.excerpt: Vice President-elect Kamala Harris hit up a Washington, DC outdoor holiday market Saturday — and found herself the perfect stocking stuffer. With husband Doug Emhoff at her side, a laughing

value.title: Trump calls on Congress to help ‘decimated’ restaurant industry
value.excerpt: President Trump took to Twitter on Friday night to urge Congress to pass the next coronavirus stimulus package and aid failing restaurants as the second wave of the pandemic is forcing some parts of the country to re-enter stricter social distancing guidelines.

value.title: Mattis did not disclose consultant role in column denouncing Trump's 'America First' policy
value.excerpt: The column did not reference the retired four-star general’s work with the Cohen Group, an international business advisory firm active in China.

value.title: Trump warns Georgia runoff boycott would play 'right into the hands of some very sick people'
value.excerpt: Trump reiterated his frequent claim that the 2020 election was a “total scam,” but urged his supporters to turn out on behalf of Georgia’s Republican Senate candidates.

value.title: Donor sues pro-Trump group for $2.5M over 'empty promises' on voter fraud
value.excerpt: A pro-Trump group is being sued by a donor for not delivering on promises to overturn the election results in President Trump's favor.

value.title: Trump team removes members of Pentagon's Defense Policy Board, including Kissinger, Albright
value.excerpt: The Defense Department on Friday said that a number of members of its Defense Policy Board -- including former Secretaries of State Henry Kissinger and Madeleine Albright -- had been removed.

value.title: Tulsi Gabbard urges Trump to grant clemency to Assange, Snowden
value.excerpt: U.S. Rep. Tulsi Gabbard has called on President Trump to pardon National Security Agency (NSA) whistleblower Edward Snowden and WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange before the president leaves office on Jan. 20, according to a report.

value.title: Defund-police supporters tell Biden they're 'not going away'
value.excerpt: Far-left advocates of defunding the police say they are "not going away" just because Joe Biden won the presidency.

value.title: Dem leaders condemn Trump's pardon of Michael Flynn: 'Abuse of power'
value.excerpt: Democratic leaders lambasted President Trump for pardoning his former national security adviser Michael Flynn on Wednesday, condemning the move as a "brazen" abuse of power.

value.title: What is President Trump doing on Thanksgiving?
value.excerpt: For the first time since he was sworn in as president nearly four years ago, President Trump will not spend Thanksgiving at his Mar-a-Lago resort in Florida.

value.title: Live Updates: Trump says he won election, repeats claims of voting irregularities
value.excerpt: President Trump called into an event held by Pennsylvania Republicans on Wednesday, where he reiterated his claim that he won the Nov. 3 election and reasserted claims of voting irregularities.

value.title: Trump campaign adviser Boris Epshteyn tests positive for coronavirus
value.excerpt: Boris Epshteyn, a campaign adviser to President Trump, announced Wednesday that he has tested positive for the novel coronavirus.

value.title: Progressive groups want 'squad member' Rashida Tlaib in Biden cabinet
value.excerpt: Progressive groups are pushing President-elect Joe Biden to include more candidates who lean further to the left than him in his cabinet, including a member of the “Squad,” as they seek influence over policymaking.

value.title: Biden says he'll push 'pathway to citizenship for over 11 million undocumented people' in first 100 days
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden has committed to forging "a pathway to citizenship for over 11 million undocumented people in America" in the first 100 days of his administration.

value.title: Matt Schlapp: Nevada allowing Trump team to present election fraud case 'a great step'
value.excerpt: Nevada is ready to hear the Trump campaign's case regarding illegal balloting allegations in Clark County, American Conservative Union chairman Matt Schlapp told “Hannity” Tuesday night.

value.title: AOC, Ilhan Omar try to block 'deficit hawk' from Biden administration
value.excerpt: Squad members Reps. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez, D-N.Y. and Ilhan Omar, D-Minn., are mounting a petition against Biden nominating his former chief of staff Bruce Reed, who they say is a “deficit hawk,” to a role within the incoming administration.

value.title: Senior Biden staffer called Palestinian suicide bombings ‘the last resort of a desperate people’
value.excerpt: Biden's pick for Deputy Director of the White House Office of Legislative Affairs referred to Palestinian suicide bombings as "the last resort of a desperate people" in 2002.

value.title: Biden emphasizes foreign policy team will 'lead the world, not retreat'
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden says that his newly named foreign policy and national security team will keep the nation "safe and secure" and will show that "America is back."

value.title: Josh Hawley criticizes Biden Cabinet picks as 'corporatists,' 'war enthusiasts' and Big Tech 'sellouts'
value.excerpt: Sen. Josh Hawley on Tuesday criticized President-elect Joe Biden's cabinet picks.

value.title: Pennsylvania certifies election results for Biden despite Trump legal challenges
value.excerpt: The Pennsylvania State Department certified the results of the presidential election in favor of President-elect Joe Biden and Vice President-elect Kamala Harris, Gov. Tom Wolf said Tuesday.

value.title: Joe Concha: Media coverage of Biden transition has been just like the campaign, 'no scrutiny'
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden’s transition period will be fawned over by the media compared with President Trump, Fox News contributor Joe Concha said on Tuesday.

value.title: Kamala Harris: Biden Cabinet Nominees Have "Unwavering Belief In America's Ideals"
value.excerpt: Elect Joe Biden's announcement of diplomatic and foreign policy cabinet picks on Tuesday. VICE PRESIDENT-ELECT KAMALA HARRIS: President-Elect Biden and I have long known that when we were elected we would inherit a series of unprecedented challenges upon walking into the White House.

value.title: Biden spotlights ‘enduring commitment’ to NATO in talk with alliance leader
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden on spoke on Monday with the head of North Atlantic Treaty Organization - better known as NATO – the more than 7 decade old security organization that bonds the U.S with much of Europe.

value.title: Biden to tap former Fed Chair Janet Yellen as Treasury secretary: report
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden will reportedly nominate former Federal Reserve Chair Janet Yellen to serve as Treasury secretary in his administration, which would make her the first female to hold the Cabinet post.

value.title: GM Stops Backing Trump Administration in Emissions Fight With California
value.excerpt: General Motors will no longer back the administration in its legal battle to strip California’s authority to set its own fuel-efficiency regulations, saying GM’s goals for green cars are aligned with the state and the new Biden administration.

value.title: Befriended by Trump, Populists in Europe’s East Brace for Change
value.excerpt: Populist and authoritarian politicians in Central Europe, who viewed President Trump as a valuable ally, are bracing for the incoming Biden administration’s new stress on promoting democracy and the rule of law.

value.title: Melania Trump celebrates arrival of annual White House Christmas tree
value.excerpt: First lady Melania Trump on Monday celebrated the arrival of the annual White House Christmas tree — without President Trump or their son Barron Trump, who have attended the event in past
